  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "To remove a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Messenger**: Launch the Messenger app on your device.\n\n2. **Search for the Contact**: In the search bar at the top, type the name of the person you want to remove. This will show you a list of conversations.\n\n3. **Open the Conversation**: Tap on the conversation with the person you want to remove.\n\n4. **Tap on the Name**: At the top of the chat, tap on the name of the person (or the profile photo) to open their profile.\n\n5. **Block or Unmatch**: If you don't want to have any interaction with them:\n   - You can choose \"Block\" to prevent them from sending you messages or seeing your profile.\n   - Alternatively, you can select \"Unmatch\" if you've had any previous interaction through features like dating or marketplace.\n\n6. **Exit the Chat**: If you only want to remove them from your contact list but still want to keep the conversation, you can simply ignore them. They won\u2019t appear in your favorites but will still be part of your message history.\n\n7. **Delete the Conversation (Optional)**: If you want to delete the conversation as well, you can do that by swiping left on the chat and selecting \"Delete\" or opening the conversation and tapping the \"i\" icon to access more options and select \"Delete Conversation.\"\n\nRemember, if you block someone, they will no longer be able to contact you, and you'll be removed from their friends' list as well. If you only want to remove them from your view without blocking, consider deleting the conversation.",
